WEBVTT

00:00.174 --> 00:05.122
♪ Hey, why is it happening ♪

00:06.094 --> 00:08.802
♪ My heart is racing ♪

00:09.934 --> 00:13.942
♪ The world has fallen silent ♪

00:13.966 --> 00:18.722
♪ Hey, when I imagine you ♪

00:19.758 --> 00:22.786
♪ What kind of look ♪

00:23.790 --> 00:27.734
♪ Attracted me to you ♪

00:27.758 --> 00:31.030
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:31.054 --> 00:34.518
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

00:34.542 --> 00:39.790
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

00:39.790 --> 00:41.408
♪ I love you ♪

00:41.408 --> 00:44.886
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:44.910 --> 00:48.182
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

00:48.206 --> 00:53.878
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

00:53.902 --> 00:55.246
♪ I love you ♪

00:55.246 --> 00:58.582
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

00:58.606 --> 01:01.954
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

01:02.062 --> 01:07.259
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

01:07.259 --> 01:08.942
♪ I love you ♪

01:08.942 --> 01:12.342
♪ Slowly, slowly, we fall in love ♪

01:12.366 --> 01:15.766
♪ Slowly, slowly, I can't leave you ♪

01:15.790 --> 01:21.366
♪ Slowly, slowly, I am with you ♪

01:21.390 --> 01:24.802
♪ I love you ♪

01:27.080 --> 01:27.878
=Love Me, Love My Voice=

01:27.902 --> 01:30.846
=Love Me, Love My Voice=
=Episode 11=

01:30.846 --> 01:34.414
(Thank you
for making me dinner, darling)

01:46.242 --> 01:47.542
This is good, too.

02:07.001 --> 02:08.342
Hello, there.

02:13.321 --> 02:14.582
Fever gone?

02:15.161 --> 02:16.702
I think so.

02:17.441 --> 02:19.661
But it may come back at night.

02:21.242 --> 02:23.522
Should we go to the hospital?

02:23.522 --> 02:29.462
No need. It happens once or twice
every year. I'll be fine tomorrow.

02:31.642 --> 02:37.661
You sweated a lot. Should I
turn on the AC? You may get a cold.

02:38.481 --> 02:40.821
No, it's okay. Thanks.

02:42.962 --> 02:45.702
Are you thirsty? Or hungry?

02:46.922 --> 02:50.381
I'm just going to the bathroom.

02:52.761 --> 02:53.761
Go ahead.

03:16.802 --> 03:21.101
Are you hungry? It's four o'clock.
Should I get a takeout?

03:24.321 --> 03:31.702
Or I can cook. I'm not much of a chef,
but I can make rice porridge.

03:33.122 --> 03:35.221
Do you like those snacks?

03:40.122 --> 03:41.661
Yeah, they're good.

03:42.962 --> 03:46.342
Which one do you like?
I'll get more of them next time.

03:47.041 --> 03:50.022
The chicken feet. And the pork jerky.

03:51.441 --> 03:56.721
Forget it. I'll bring some snacks
and food from our supermarket.

03:56.721 --> 03:58.981
Okay, let me pay.

03:59.761 --> 04:01.061
No need.

04:02.402 --> 04:06.342
Sit a bit. I'll go lie down.
I'm still dizzy.

04:23.882 --> 04:26.002
You sweated a lot. Have some water.

04:26.002 --> 04:28.181
Okay, thank you.

04:42.121 --> 04:43.421
I think you're fine.

04:45.002 --> 04:46.342
Your hair clipper.

04:47.002 --> 04:48.142
Let me help.

05:00.281 --> 05:03.022
- Done.
- Thanks.

05:07.121 --> 05:09.462
It's stuck on my watch.

05:10.481 --> 05:12.661
Don't move. Let me get it off.

05:26.442 --> 05:27.462
Wait.

05:40.281 --> 05:41.382
It hurts?

05:45.681 --> 05:47.062
Stay still.

05:51.962 --> 05:53.062
Almost done.

05:59.681 --> 06:07.681
Should we turn on the light first?

06:09.041 --> 06:13.062
Should I close the door for you?

06:13.681 --> 06:15.221
Turn on the light.

06:21.281 --> 06:22.621
Are you okay?

06:23.962 --> 06:24.882
I'm fine.

06:24.882 --> 06:27.301
I'm sorry.

06:29.361 --> 06:30.422
You finished the script?

06:30.422 --> 06:33.242
Yeah, I'm looking for something to eat.

06:33.242 --> 06:37.301
Otherwise,
I wouldn't have disrupted you.

06:42.721 --> 06:45.502
He's been here all along?

06:47.082 --> 06:48.082
Yeah.

06:48.921 --> 06:54.014
You came here,
so I texted him to stay in his room.

06:54.014 --> 06:58.358
I didn't want you to be awkward.

06:58.382 --> 07:03.142
I'm a good boy. I wouldn't come out
if I weren't starving.

07:04.202 --> 07:09.702
We were talking about what to eat.
Let's have dinner together.

07:10.241 --> 07:12.862
Mo, can I join you?

07:12.862 --> 07:15.421
As long as you want to.

07:16.442 --> 07:19.142
Alright, then. Thank you.

07:24.522 --> 07:30.942
Let's have rice porridge. You have rice,
right? I'll make some light dishes.

07:32.481 --> 07:35.142
I want steamed beef with rice flour.

07:37.601 --> 07:39.361
(I don't know how to make it.)

07:39.361 --> 07:42.842
Aren't you supposed to
have something light?

07:42.842 --> 07:44.342
Okay?

07:46.161 --> 07:49.541
Next time, okay? You're having a fever.

07:50.762 --> 07:53.661
I have the ingredients ready.

07:55.601 --> 07:59.262
My fever is gone. Let me cook for you.

07:59.262 --> 08:00.722
Alright, alright.

08:00.722 --> 08:06.981
You should eat light. You're a doctor.
You should know that. Talk to him.

08:07.642 --> 08:10.942
I can't cook.
I'll be grateful no matter who cooks.

08:12.442 --> 08:17.462
- Let me. But you can't have too much.
- Okay.

08:24.322 --> 08:24.922
This one?

08:24.922 --> 08:26.381
I think so.

08:27.881 --> 08:31.501
It's frozen. How do we cook it?
Shouldn't we defrost it?

08:33.042 --> 08:36.642
Shall we heat it in the microwave oven?

08:36.642 --> 08:38.441
I don't think so.

08:38.441 --> 08:41.021
It will be defrosted in a minute.

08:42.802 --> 08:45.842
Then the meat will lose texture.

08:45.842 --> 08:47.902
So what do we do?

08:47.902 --> 08:52.901
Keep it in the plastic bag
and leave it in cold water.

09:13.162 --> 09:15.021
He's got everything.

09:15.761 --> 09:19.962
He could have been a great chef
instead of a doctor.

09:19.962 --> 09:23.901
But he can't make
a habit into a job, right?

09:24.601 --> 09:25.762
I guess.

09:25.762 --> 09:29.101
You know what? Mo...

09:32.721 --> 09:34.442
We're waiting for it to defrost.

09:34.442 --> 09:35.981
We're not slacking off.

09:42.802 --> 09:43.941
It's not ready?

09:43.941 --> 09:46.741
Yeah, it's only been ten minutes.

10:09.761 --> 10:13.261
Check it out. Three-star Michelin chef.

10:25.521 --> 10:29.221
Baking soda. Cooking wine.
And chopsticks, please.

10:29.962 --> 10:32.022
Baking soda.

10:32.022 --> 10:33.462
Chopsticks.

10:35.121 --> 10:36.542
Okay, thank you.

10:47.202 --> 10:48.381
Flavored water.

10:48.962 --> 10:50.042
Flavored water.

10:50.042 --> 10:51.122
Flavored water.

10:51.122 --> 10:56.001
I don't know where that is.
He runs the kitchen here.

10:56.001 --> 10:57.942
It's over there.

11:00.922 --> 11:05.422
This one? I see scallions.
I think that's it.

11:08.881 --> 11:10.321
When did you make it?

11:10.321 --> 11:11.822
At noon.

11:13.082 --> 11:15.382
Weren't you having a fever?

11:15.382 --> 11:18.621
I was craving it,
so I prepared it in advance.

11:19.641 --> 11:21.182
Oyster sauce. Soy sauce.

11:21.922 --> 11:25.261
- Oyster sauce.
- Here.

11:26.601 --> 11:30.261
- Soybean paste. And oil.
- Alright.

11:37.282 --> 11:38.542
Mix them.

11:46.442 --> 11:48.242
Do you need me here?

11:48.242 --> 11:49.822
Not really.

11:52.562 --> 11:55.662
I'll take my medicine. Watch the time.

11:58.881 --> 12:02.381
Marinate it for ten minutes.
Call me when it's ready.

12:07.082 --> 12:11.774
Thank goodness you're here.
I'm starting to be convinced that

12:11.774 --> 12:14.277
I'm benefiting the most
from your relationship.

12:14.301 --> 12:18.942
I'd be helping him with cooking
if you weren't here.

12:19.682 --> 12:21.042
I don't cook very well.

12:21.042 --> 12:25.042
It doesn't matter. He's a genius chef.
That's what matters.

12:25.042 --> 12:29.342
He gets the meat and greens he likes
when we go for the groceries.

12:29.342 --> 12:33.821
Then he finds recipes and studies them.

12:33.821 --> 12:38.381
He gets the ingredients first
and then looks for recipes?

12:39.601 --> 12:42.262
What a fancy foodie.

12:42.262 --> 12:47.182
You don't get it. He's not "fancy".
He's "superb". Okay?

12:50.241 --> 12:52.662
- We'll have rice porridge.
- Okay.

12:53.842 --> 12:54.741
Where's the rice?

12:54.741 --> 12:56.221
Over there.

12:58.682 --> 13:01.782
You know the kitchen better than me now.

13:19.121 --> 13:20.342
Well, Sheng.

13:21.361 --> 13:24.782
Do you know about
that "repost" incident a few years ago?

13:26.282 --> 13:32.222
Of course, that's his only scandal.
And they keep bringing it up.

13:32.222 --> 13:39.082
Someone lost his pet and asked him
to repost, but it was a fraud.

13:39.082 --> 13:43.622
He deleted the repost and apologized,
but they kept saying that

13:43.622 --> 13:48.521
he had planned the whole thing
for money, fame, attention,

13:48.521 --> 13:49.861
and...

13:53.922 --> 13:57.886
Fame brought him unwanted attention.

13:57.886 --> 14:02.066
I felt so sorry for him back then.

14:02.721 --> 14:06.521
The netizens cursed him for three months
but even doxxed him.

14:06.521 --> 14:12.282
Yeah, he didn't want to implicate
the hospital and his patients.

14:12.282 --> 14:16.602
So he dropped out for three years.

14:16.602 --> 14:18.101
What a pity.

14:18.101 --> 14:22.782
I still can't read DMs
because of what happened to him.

14:22.782 --> 14:28.322
I ignore all those posts mentioning me
because I don't want any trouble.

14:28.322 --> 14:32.342
It's the same for Mo.
He's ignoring all the gossip.

14:32.342 --> 14:39.962
That's hatred brewed by jealousy.
And it's irrational, isn't it?

14:39.962 --> 14:47.962
So we'd better leave it to time
and ignore those people online, right?

14:51.202 --> 14:55.782
- Are you consolidating me?
- Yeah.

15:02.202 --> 15:04.182
It wasn't very pleasant

15:06.282 --> 15:08.062
to read those at first.

15:08.922 --> 15:14.761
I never had so many fans.
No one knew me. I was nobody.

15:14.761 --> 15:19.101
So many people started cursing me
out of the blue.

15:21.442 --> 15:23.582
I wasn't used to it.

15:24.682 --> 15:26.141
I'll get over it.

15:28.601 --> 15:31.981
And I forgot about it
once I heard that he got sick.

15:32.962 --> 15:39.301
Good for you. Those people hide behind
their screens and spread rumors all day.

15:39.301 --> 15:42.422
The best way to deal with them
is to ignore them.

15:44.721 --> 15:46.261
Let me see.

15:48.241 --> 15:52.381
Should we cook
some mushrooms with greens?

15:53.001 --> 15:55.621
Alright, as long as you don't
mind my cooking skills.

15:55.621 --> 15:58.141
I bet you're better than me.

15:58.842 --> 16:00.642
Good luck. I'll be in my room.

16:00.642 --> 16:01.901
Alright.

16:07.282 --> 16:14.221
Steamed beef. Mushrooms with greens.
Recipes. Let me find the recipes.

16:20.641 --> 16:21.702
It's dead.

16:42.682 --> 16:43.922
It's ready?

16:43.922 --> 16:50.861
No, my phone died. I want to search
for the recipes. May I use your PC?

16:52.521 --> 16:54.502
Use my tablet. It's easier.

17:08.641 --> 17:11.801
Don't get out of bed so often.
You may get worse.

17:11.801 --> 17:16.542
My fever is gone. It's only
my throat hurting. So it's fine.

17:17.722 --> 17:21.062
I couldn't get out of bed all day
when I had a fever.

17:26.161 --> 17:32.101
I once worked all night right after
the fever was gone.

17:33.401 --> 17:37.101
Didn't your parents feel sorry for you?

17:37.921 --> 17:42.842
Not really. A liver transplant surgeon
and a cardiac surgeon.

17:42.842 --> 17:49.222
It'd be lucky if they could meet
once a week for dinner.

17:49.802 --> 17:52.701
So they didn't feel for me.

17:57.121 --> 17:58.181
Found it?

18:01.842 --> 18:06.082
Add ground rice flour to beef
and mix them well.

18:06.082 --> 18:13.036
Place them on steamer.
Steam on a big fire for 12 minutes.

18:13.060 --> 18:14.770
Is that right?

18:16.121 --> 18:19.982
The ground rice flour
is next to the flavored water.

18:36.762 --> 18:41.381
Thank you for making me dinner, darling.

18:47.601 --> 18:49.262
Thanks for keeping me company.

18:51.802 --> 18:57.381
I just don't want you
to be alone at home.

18:58.842 --> 19:00.941
You may need help.

19:18.601 --> 19:22.062
Alright, I'll go cook.

20:09.641 --> 20:12.661
What's wrong with your eyes?

20:13.562 --> 20:14.941
Need an ophthalmologist?

20:15.601 --> 20:17.502
Let me check them for you.

20:18.242 --> 20:22.181
- Don't get cocky, Mr. Boyfriend.
- Are you jealous?

20:24.441 --> 20:25.901
Very much.

20:29.641 --> 20:32.521
I prepared some tofu just in case
we didn't have enough dishes.

20:32.521 --> 20:33.262
Thank you.

20:33.262 --> 20:34.461
Chopsticks.

20:38.441 --> 20:41.502
Some of us are born luckier.

20:41.502 --> 20:43.342
Get lost.

20:44.042 --> 20:45.222
Have some rice porridge.

20:45.222 --> 20:46.742
Thank you.

20:46.742 --> 20:48.222
Sheng.

20:50.042 --> 20:51.302
Thank you.

20:55.121 --> 20:56.222
No problem.

20:57.601 --> 20:59.022
Be right back.

21:03.681 --> 21:05.941
Mo, you're really something.

21:06.961 --> 21:09.742
Sheng, thank you.

21:18.601 --> 21:19.382
What?

21:19.382 --> 21:21.621
I want the first bite.

21:24.681 --> 21:25.941
Here we go.

21:28.522 --> 21:30.202
I asked for this dish.

21:30.202 --> 21:32.222
Why aren't you eating?

21:32.222 --> 21:33.822
We're talking about...

21:33.822 --> 21:35.802
We're talking about

21:35.802 --> 21:38.782
whether we should use spoons
for rice porridge and tofu.

21:39.401 --> 21:40.722
Oh right, let me get them.

21:40.722 --> 21:44.302
Don't. I can't let you
do all the work. I'll go.

21:46.401 --> 21:48.662
Where are the spoons?

21:48.662 --> 21:50.661
No idea. Look around.

21:56.322 --> 21:58.081
He doesn't eat scallions?

21:58.081 --> 22:02.502
No way. He'll eat grass
if that's what you feed him.

22:04.961 --> 22:07.982
The steamed beef
will be ready. I'll check on it.

22:10.002 --> 22:10.962
Dig in.

22:10.962 --> 22:12.502
I'll wait for you.

22:21.961 --> 22:25.661
There's nothing you won't say
to please your girlfriend, huh?

22:26.562 --> 22:31.022
But it's okay. I can eat grass.
I can eat anything you feed me.

22:32.361 --> 22:35.542
Someone's very talkative today.

22:36.361 --> 22:40.982
I've been in my room all day.
I'm happy to see all these nice dishes.

22:40.982 --> 22:43.021
I get talkative when I'm happy.

22:43.021 --> 22:47.342
I got sick and earned this meal.
Try to contain yourself.

22:47.881 --> 22:50.901
Fine, I will. So petty.

22:52.722 --> 22:56.901
Who is it? Wang Ke.
Should I invite him over?

23:00.082 --> 23:03.701
Okay, I'm the third wheel.
We don't need a fourth one.

23:04.401 --> 23:07.582
Who's Wang Ke? Your friend?
I don't know him.

23:19.842 --> 23:21.202
Anybody coming?

23:21.202 --> 23:23.022
No.

23:25.722 --> 23:28.022
He doesn't answer.
How do we get up there?

23:28.022 --> 23:35.041
How would I know? Why did you have to
ride an electrocar? We're freezing here.

23:35.041 --> 23:37.542
Move. Let me sit a bit.

23:37.542 --> 23:38.822
Hey...

23:39.441 --> 23:44.322
Stop nagging me. Why should I drive?
Where do we park? There's a parking fee.

23:44.322 --> 23:49.802
And the gas? This is eco-friendly.
Charge it once and it runs for a week.

23:49.802 --> 23:55.542
Shut up. Why do you have so much to say?
Figure out how to get up there, okay?

23:58.762 --> 24:02.181
Is it inhabited?
Why isn't there anyone coming out?

24:06.201 --> 24:08.402
Could Mo Qingcheng pass out in his room?

24:08.402 --> 24:09.702
No way.

24:09.702 --> 24:11.282
Call the ambulance.

24:11.282 --> 24:15.701
Still, I don't think the medical staff
can get up there.

24:16.282 --> 24:17.582
What do you think?

24:19.921 --> 24:21.661
They can't open the door.

24:36.842 --> 24:38.782
Is this old man from this building?

24:38.782 --> 24:42.141
Of course. It's the only building here.

24:42.141 --> 24:44.102
What if he's just walking around?

24:44.102 --> 24:48.742
With groceries? Look, he's getting
his keys out, right?

24:48.742 --> 24:55.682
He's turning. Come on.
Sir, do you live here?

24:55.682 --> 24:57.262
Yeah.

24:57.262 --> 24:58.902
Great, let me help.

24:58.902 --> 25:00.262
What's going on?

25:01.921 --> 25:03.701
What do you want?

25:03.701 --> 25:08.542
Sir, please don't be mad.
Our friend lives in this building.

25:08.542 --> 25:12.561
He's having a fever and doesn't answer
our call, so we're worried.

25:12.561 --> 25:15.342
Could you please open the door for us?

25:15.342 --> 25:16.582
Yeah.

25:25.201 --> 25:27.461
What do you do? Why should I trust you?

25:41.082 --> 25:43.222
What's wrong with your friend?

25:46.482 --> 25:47.301
Where are you going?

25:47.301 --> 25:48.782
I'll bring the dishes.

25:49.961 --> 25:52.141
So considerate.

25:59.601 --> 26:00.661
Let me.

26:05.802 --> 26:06.901
Here.

26:08.921 --> 26:10.082
Let me clean up a bit.

26:10.082 --> 26:14.222
No need. Come and eat.
Juemei will clean up later.

26:14.222 --> 26:17.802
Yeah, Ieave them for me.
I'm in charge of the cleaning.

26:17.802 --> 26:19.022
Alright.

26:23.201 --> 26:29.142
Let's thank Shengshengman
for these dishes with a toast.

26:29.142 --> 26:31.661
Come on, that's enough. Dig in.

26:33.522 --> 26:36.181
Let me try the steamed beef.

26:38.601 --> 26:39.861
Me too.

26:45.441 --> 26:47.542
You sure you haven't made this before?

26:49.361 --> 26:50.602
It's good.

26:50.602 --> 26:52.181
Really?

26:53.042 --> 26:59.461
The girlfriend of the superb foodie
is also superb. Let me try this.

27:02.762 --> 27:04.062
You're gifted.

27:04.062 --> 27:08.461
Seriously,
it's pretty impressive for a new chef.

27:09.401 --> 27:10.502
You should eat more.

27:10.502 --> 27:11.482
Alright, of course.

27:11.482 --> 27:13.762
You're having a fever.
Have some rice porridge.

27:13.762 --> 27:14.842
Alright.

27:14.842 --> 27:20.842
Your voice is so hoarse. You'd better
recover by the next anniversary event.

27:20.842 --> 27:22.482
Just eat. Don't talk about work.

27:22.482 --> 27:28.422
I got a cold some days ago and did
a check-up. Take a look at the report.

27:28.422 --> 27:29.762
Sure, bring it here.

27:29.762 --> 27:31.302
Just a second.

27:33.601 --> 27:34.921
Well done.

27:34.921 --> 27:37.521
You prepared the sauce.

27:37.521 --> 27:39.421
The rice porridge is also nice.

27:41.242 --> 27:45.982
Here's the report. Take a look.
It cost me a fortune.

27:57.121 --> 27:58.301
What's wrong?

28:01.961 --> 28:03.461
You have a problem.

28:04.441 --> 28:05.542
What is it?

28:09.921 --> 28:15.861
You talk too much and eat too much.
You may get a fatty liver.

28:17.921 --> 28:22.282
Sheng, he feeds me so well. I'd be lucky
if I didn't get a fatty liver, right?

28:22.282 --> 28:26.781
You need vegetable intake.
And have some grains.

28:26.781 --> 28:31.661
I did. Corn flour, grain porridge
or something when he's not home.

28:32.401 --> 28:33.801
That's it. You're fine.

28:33.801 --> 28:40.702
Alright, come to think about it. Sheng,
be very careful once you marry him...

28:40.702 --> 28:42.582
What's wrong?

28:45.401 --> 28:48.962
Nothing. It's burning and I forgot.

28:48.962 --> 28:50.701
Slow down.

28:51.522 --> 28:54.961
It's burning. Cool it down for her.

28:54.961 --> 28:57.101
Stop talking or you'll get fatty liver.

29:00.282 --> 29:01.302
Who is it?

29:03.522 --> 29:04.661
Let me see.

29:06.681 --> 29:07.802
- What's wrong?
- It's you?

29:07.802 --> 29:10.762
- Why don't you pick up?
- Shoes off.

29:10.762 --> 29:11.322
Seriously.

29:11.322 --> 29:12.722
We were worried sick.

29:12.722 --> 29:13.282
He...

29:13.282 --> 29:15.401
What are you doing
behind Shengshengman's back?

29:15.401 --> 29:16.701
So annoying.

29:21.921 --> 29:23.142
Hello, Sheng.

29:23.142 --> 29:24.422
Hello, there.

29:24.422 --> 29:27.661
- We're worried about you.
- Yeah.

29:28.601 --> 29:31.661
Have you eaten? Want to join us?

29:31.661 --> 29:32.601
Shall we...

29:32.601 --> 29:34.302
O-Okay.

29:34.302 --> 29:36.522
- I'll get you some rice porridge.
- No need.

29:36.522 --> 29:38.822
- Thanks.
- They got this.

29:45.201 --> 29:49.302
That's impressive. We keep running
into your girlfriend here.

29:49.302 --> 29:54.174
Not bad. That explains the fever.
He's faking it to lure her here.

29:54.174 --> 29:56.522
What a bad boy.

29:56.522 --> 30:00.502
I was wondering how he got sick.
He never gets sick.

30:00.502 --> 30:04.342
Are you eating or not?

30:05.842 --> 30:07.302
We are.

30:09.522 --> 30:13.062
Wang Ke, I just washed the dishes
and you took my lane?

30:13.062 --> 30:14.681
Let me farm.

30:14.681 --> 30:15.921
But you're a support.

30:15.921 --> 30:17.742
I... Leave me alone.

30:19.762 --> 30:21.082
Zheng, nice hairstyle.

30:21.082 --> 30:22.161
You look good.

30:22.161 --> 30:23.002
So formal at home?

30:23.002 --> 30:25.682
Let's go to the studio.
We have work to do.

30:25.682 --> 30:26.521
What work?

30:26.521 --> 30:27.242
Urgent work.

30:27.242 --> 30:30.342
I'm stuffed and I washed the dishes.
I'm sitting to digest.

30:30.342 --> 30:33.262
I said it was urgent.

30:35.441 --> 30:37.482
Sorry about that. Sheng, see you.

30:37.482 --> 30:39.522
- Cut the crap.
- Take care of her.

30:39.522 --> 30:40.881
Let me put on my shoes.

30:40.881 --> 30:42.242
Shut up. Take them out.

30:42.242 --> 30:45.822
- My bag. Wait, I left my bag in there.
- My shoes.

31:02.002 --> 31:03.421
Should we do something?

31:05.401 --> 31:06.742
I don't mind.

31:11.002 --> 31:13.242
I'll clean up the room a bit.

31:13.242 --> 31:14.582
Okay.

31:28.842 --> 31:34.542
I don't have something to entertain you.
What do you do in your spare time?

31:36.441 --> 31:37.502
I don't know.

31:39.762 --> 31:46.621
I mean, nothing specific.
I just watch movies and stuff.

31:48.361 --> 31:50.461
I haven't watched movies
for a long time.

31:51.322 --> 31:52.622
Let me check the recommendations.

31:52.622 --> 31:53.982
No need.

31:55.802 --> 31:57.062
You're bored?

31:57.601 --> 32:03.701
No, I mean, you don't need to search.
We can just watch anything.

32:04.842 --> 32:07.502
Alright, then.

32:09.282 --> 32:10.282
Let's go.

32:13.961 --> 32:16.421
We're forced to wander around.

32:19.161 --> 32:20.682
Look, so sweet.

32:20.682 --> 32:22.342
So sweet.

32:23.361 --> 32:27.302
They're having a nice time at home.
And we're freezing out here.

32:27.302 --> 32:30.962
It's going to take a while.
Let's go somewhere for fun.

32:30.962 --> 32:34.902
There's nowhere to go.
And I can only take one of you.

32:34.902 --> 32:37.622
It's not nice to dump
one of you here, right?

32:37.622 --> 32:39.202
Just leave the electrocar here.

32:39.202 --> 32:44.242
No way. It's new. What if it's stolen?
Will you make it up to me?

32:44.242 --> 32:46.121
Fine, stay close to your baby.

32:46.121 --> 32:47.622
That's what I'm doing.

32:47.622 --> 32:52.782
Zheng, let's get a cab to my place.
I set up a new PC.

32:53.641 --> 32:56.302
I'm not going there. It's too far.

32:57.921 --> 33:00.022
Fine, my place is too far.

33:13.201 --> 33:14.241
Thank you.

33:17.242 --> 33:19.782
(Sis, check out the photo I took.)

33:20.641 --> 33:21.842
(Not bad.)

33:21.842 --> 33:23.701
(Good, huh? Zoom in.)

33:25.641 --> 33:27.802
(It's weird to talk about
recipes now, right?)

33:27.802 --> 33:30.582
(Should I find something to talk about?)

33:37.401 --> 33:40.302
Well, I've charged your phone.

33:51.562 --> 33:53.302
Let me make some warm milk tea.

34:35.561 --> 34:36.481
Who is it?

34:36.481 --> 34:38.722
(Moqingcheng)
(What do you do with girls?)

34:38.722 --> 34:40.861
There's something Mo doesn't know?

34:41.481 --> 34:42.501
What's wrong?

34:47.162 --> 34:49.061
(Anything you want.)

34:53.361 --> 34:54.581
(Be serious.)

34:55.441 --> 34:57.362
That's so simple. Talk to her.

34:57.362 --> 34:58.021
Watch a movie.

34:58.021 --> 34:58.742
LARP games.

34:58.742 --> 34:59.441
Room escape.

34:59.441 --> 35:00.202
Or amusement park.

35:00.202 --> 35:01.401
So many options.

35:01.401 --> 35:02.222
Seriously.

35:02.222 --> 35:03.382
Talk to him. Here.

35:03.382 --> 35:04.382
Sorry, bro.

35:04.382 --> 35:05.982
No, no.

35:05.982 --> 35:07.702
I'm just saying.

35:11.162 --> 35:15.762
(Talk, movie, LARP games,
room escape, or amusement park.)

35:15.762 --> 35:17.861
(Too late for the amusement park.)

35:19.162 --> 35:20.221
It's getting dark.

35:20.221 --> 35:21.642
So picky.

35:21.642 --> 35:25.481
(Bro, it's getting dark.
Of course, it's too late.)

35:25.481 --> 35:29.262
(People get up early for that.
I'll book tickets for you next time.)

35:31.162 --> 35:33.822
(Nothing useful.)

35:33.822 --> 35:38.342
Zheng, you dragged us out
and he's talking to you like that?

35:38.342 --> 35:41.702
I wouldn't put up with it if I were you.

35:42.441 --> 35:43.202
Me neither.

35:43.202 --> 35:44.541
Call him.

35:49.634 --> 35:51.593
(Incoming call: Zhou Zheng)

35:52.602 --> 35:54.022
What's your problem?

35:54.022 --> 35:57.282
It's the weekend and we're freezing
out here to secure your privacy.

35:57.282 --> 36:00.442
You didn't thank us and you have
a problem with my suggestions?

36:00.442 --> 36:02.942
Thanks. That's it.

36:02.942 --> 36:04.262
What?

36:06.122 --> 36:07.022
Thanks?

36:07.022 --> 36:08.422
He hung up?

36:08.422 --> 36:09.461
Yeah.

36:11.521 --> 36:12.822
What's so funny?

36:13.441 --> 36:14.442
Outrageous.

36:14.442 --> 36:15.622
Outrageous.

36:15.622 --> 36:18.202
I'm heading to the studio. You're free.

36:18.202 --> 36:20.322
Thanks, that's what
I've been waiting for.

36:20.322 --> 36:22.242
- We can't just leave.
- Yeah.

36:22.242 --> 36:23.322
I can't carry you both.

36:23.322 --> 36:24.862
Feishao, let's play games.

36:24.862 --> 36:27.062
Get out of my sight. So annoying.

36:27.062 --> 36:28.822
Will do.

36:28.822 --> 36:31.061
Tell us when you get to the studio.

36:51.361 --> 36:52.261
Be careful. It's hot.

36:52.261 --> 36:53.501
Thanks.

36:56.682 --> 37:00.182
Is it new merch? It looks so nice.

37:00.182 --> 37:04.342
I was their dubbing director.
I think it's only for staff.

37:05.921 --> 37:07.302
It's so special.

37:08.202 --> 37:10.061
I'll wash it. Take it home.

37:11.242 --> 37:13.222
I didn't mean to take it home.

37:13.222 --> 37:16.102
I know. But you like it.

37:16.722 --> 37:19.042
Still, I can't just take it from you.

37:19.042 --> 37:22.581
Don't be shy.
It's not like we're strangers.

37:59.802 --> 38:01.622
The milk tea is so nice.

38:01.622 --> 38:04.182
Pack some before you leave.

38:04.182 --> 38:07.622
No need. Just tell me the brand.
I'll get some.

38:10.322 --> 38:12.182
I mean, at our supermarket.

38:12.762 --> 38:18.241
I should try things for our customers.
That's part of our jobs.

38:18.241 --> 38:22.501
You have a great reputation.
My colleagues speak highly of you.

38:23.322 --> 38:28.822
Yeah, many retired doctors
still ask us for delivery.

38:28.822 --> 38:30.082
Really?

38:30.082 --> 38:31.562
Don't you know?

38:31.562 --> 38:33.501
I was transferred here.

38:34.081 --> 38:35.222
Okay.

39:35.242 --> 39:38.142
Let me find something else to eat.

40:06.722 --> 40:08.532
(Pork Mooncake)
Their mooncakes are famous.

40:08.532 --> 40:10.342
(Pork Mooncake)
They always have a long line.

40:10.342 --> 40:11.342
Really?

40:11.342 --> 40:13.622
Want some? My treat.

40:15.282 --> 40:17.082
But we have to wait. Is it fine?

40:17.082 --> 40:18.822
It's fine. It's my day off.

40:18.822 --> 40:20.501
Let's line up, then.

40:32.361 --> 40:33.461
Dad.

40:34.802 --> 40:37.222
Sheng.

40:38.322 --> 40:39.501
Sheng.

40:40.322 --> 40:41.421
Sheng.

40:42.602 --> 40:43.662
Sheng.

40:44.802 --> 40:46.062
I knew it was you.

40:46.062 --> 40:46.882
Dad.

40:46.882 --> 40:49.142
You didn't hear me?

40:50.722 --> 40:51.902
No.

40:51.902 --> 40:53.201
Geez.

40:53.201 --> 40:55.581
Want some pork mooncakes?

40:56.561 --> 40:59.582
Your mom got some this afternoon.
Hop on. Let's go home.

40:59.582 --> 41:01.021
No.

41:02.961 --> 41:07.182
My classmates are coming.
I'm lining up for them.

41:07.182 --> 41:11.822
I was bragging to them
about the pork mooncakes here.

41:11.822 --> 41:13.722
Go home. I'll be home soon.

41:13.722 --> 41:17.202
Your mom got a whole pack of those.
It's too many for us.

41:17.202 --> 41:20.362
Tell your friends to pass by
our house and pick up some. Hop on.

41:20.362 --> 41:22.222
No. Dad.

41:23.361 --> 41:25.262
It has to be hot.

41:27.081 --> 41:29.721
There's something wrong with you.

41:29.721 --> 41:36.321
You never line up here even if
we tell you to. What's going on today?

41:36.321 --> 41:38.061
There is no such thing.

41:42.921 --> 41:44.262
The line is moving.

41:51.162 --> 41:52.421
Go ahead.

41:56.481 --> 42:00.561
Dad, go home. I'll be home soon.

42:00.561 --> 42:03.741
But I'm coming out for groceries.

42:03.741 --> 42:05.122
Well, go get the groceries.

42:05.122 --> 42:06.342
See you later.

42:06.342 --> 42:07.881
Bye.

42:07.881 --> 42:09.342
See you.

42:13.041 --> 42:16.322
You scared me to death, you know?
Why did you pat me?

42:16.322 --> 42:19.742
I thought my dad recognized you or...

42:34.361 --> 42:38.941
Dad, didn't you go shopping?
Why are you back?

43:22.829 --> 43:28.229
♪ Turning the years into a drifting boat ♪

43:28.253 --> 43:33.339
♪ Sailing through
the tumult and winding sorrow ♪

43:33.597 --> 43:38.759
♪ I fear that the past will be crushed
by the coming cold wind ♪

43:38.759 --> 43:44.865
♪ And stirred into
a piece of tranquil river water ♪

43:47.197 --> 43:52.444
♪ Touching the crack with my fingertips ♪

43:52.444 --> 43:57.554
♪ I dare not look at the haggard faces
and gray hair in the mirror ♪

43:57.554 --> 44:03.271
♪ After many years,
the longing remains as sharp ♪

44:03.271 --> 44:08.793
♪ And our shadows are thinner ♪

44:08.793 --> 44:12.103
♪ Grinding the memories into ink ♪

44:12.103 --> 44:14.671
♪ And writing them on the paper ♪

44:14.671 --> 44:16.775
♪ The mirror and the person
are both gone ♪

44:16.775 --> 44:19.495
♪ Where could I ask for the return date ♪

44:19.495 --> 44:22.665
♪ The bronze mirror shatters at farewell ♪

44:22.665 --> 44:24.839
♪ It's hard to convey the lovesickness ♪

44:24.839 --> 44:29.467
♪ Over millions of miles ♪

44:30.045 --> 44:33.607
♪ I laugh at the fame
and wealth of my life ♪

44:33.607 --> 44:35.586
♪ I picture it as a flower in the mirror ♪

44:35.586 --> 44:40.711
♪ It's hard to rival
a cup of tea in your hand ♪

44:40.711 --> 44:42.343
♪ We drink from the same cup ♪

44:42.343 --> 44:44.295
♪ And we share joy and sorrow ♪

44:44.295 --> 44:47.148
♪ We drink down the past memories ♪

44:47.148 --> 44:51.815
♪ Being together from morning till night ♪

44:51.815 --> 44:55.175
♪ Or alone in the corner of the world ♪

44:55.175 --> 44:57.182
♪ Frost whitens the hair
in front of the forehead ♪

44:57.182 --> 45:02.343
♪ Looking at the world, where is my home ♪

45:02.343 --> 45:04.947
♪ I wish the clear frost
glitter in the moonlight ♪

45:04.947 --> 45:08.669
♪ Reflecting the couple in the mirror ♪

45:08.669 --> 45:13.755
♪ Return with you ♪

45:14.397 --> 45:20.069
♪ After being separated for half a life ♪
